Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.09,0:00:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.83,0:00:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We just have to\Ncover it up well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.27,0:00:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'd like to have a drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.44,0:00:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I have some whiskey bonbons.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.27,0:00:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say that.\NIt's a gift from a real beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.68,0:00:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?\NYou look depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.42,0:00:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe\Nanything anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.69,0:00:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll listen if you want me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.96,0:00:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I believed in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.53,0:00:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think that Inspector Zeman\Nwould do such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.07,0:00:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.54,0:00:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I believed in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.21,0:01:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now,\Nmy only peace of mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.96,0:01:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.12,0:02:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}An unbelievably dreadful event has\Ntaken place in the Prague police station!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.12,0:02:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Chief Hamrik, Detective Patella\Nand Detective Janacek{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.46,0:03:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}were found fatally poisoned.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.90,0:03:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why would their murderer want to\Ncommit such a brazen act?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.74,0:03:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,According to some rumors,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.61,0:03:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the police force has a dark connection\Nwith the former secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.74,0:03:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Will this incident be the cause\Nof an even bigger scandal?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.02,0:03:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Someone's coming out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.29,0:03:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know who\Nthe murderer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.42,0:03:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that the drug used to commit\Nthe murder was a muscle relaxant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.32,0:03:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true that even Chief Hamrik was\Ninvolved with the secret police?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.93,0:03:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh... Well...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.03,0:03:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}ls there a connection to\Ninspector Zeman's murder last week?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.57,0:03:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}W-We're investigating\Nthat at the moment.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.91,0:03:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Does that mean that\Nthe investigative department{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.94,0:03:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}believes that all of\Nthe incidents are linked?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.98,0:03:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Well... We're going to\Ninvestigate that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.58,0:03:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm very sorry\NHe's in charge of a different case.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.16,0:04:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say anything unnecessary.\NJust go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.56,0:04:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.76,0:04:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When are you going to hold\Nan official press conference ?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.60,0:04:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We will have press conference\Nwhen we gather enough information.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.67,0:04:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please wait until then.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.90,0:04:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're taking too long\Nto deal with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.52,0:04:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.42,0:04:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this another questioning?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.83,0:04:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.90,0:04:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was told by my superiors to investigate\Nthis case from the bottom up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.30,0:04:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already finished\Nquestioning the children
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.30,0:04:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,who were taken to\Nthe other orphanages.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.54,0:04:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.61,0:04:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pedrov raised them\Nas if he were their father.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.44,0:04:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They saw him and his maid die\Nright before their eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.68,0:05:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, some of them\Ncry at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.59,0:05:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to make them forget\Nthat as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.33,0:05:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not something\None can forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.93,0:05:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone that they loved\Nwas killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.87,0:05:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,15 minutes with each child.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.31,0:05:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask questions that\Nare too detailed. Got it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.95,0:05:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It was fun living there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.62,0:05:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pedrov and Mrs. Anna\Nwere really nice people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.99,0:05:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I see... I'd like to talk to you\Nabout the day of the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.29,0:05:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer came that day.\NDid he come before?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.23,0:05:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No. That was the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.27,0:05:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did he come?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.23,0:05:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.10,0:05:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Was Mr. Grimmer friendly\Nwith Mr. Pedrov?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.07,0:06:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... They didn't seem\Nvery friendly, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.74,0:06:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.84,0:06:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They were talking about something\Ndifficult to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.58,0:06:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You know a little German, don't you?\NWhat did they talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.79,0:06:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They said that this place\Nwas "unauthorized"...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.06,0:06:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and "report" to the "police."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.96,0:06:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Mr. Grimmer say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.96,0:06:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.06,0:06:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He also said "education" or something\Nand "experiment."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.83,0:06:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"Experiment"...\NAnything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.20,0:06:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.91,0:06:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to remember\Nif you don't want to, Honza.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.71,0:06:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Also "511 Kinderheim!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.48,0:06:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,511 Kinderheim?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.02,0:06:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know where that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.69,0:06:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.75,0:06:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.69,0:06:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no such place in\Nthe Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.36,0:06:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.26,0:06:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, about Mr. Grimmer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.70,0:06:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of person was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.70,0:06:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He was really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.14,0:07:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You too, huh, Izzy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.50,0:07:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We played soccer together!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.54,0:07:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.01,0:07:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But Mr. Grimmer looked like\Nhe was having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.95,0:07:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,His header was so bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.18,0:07:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He fell on his butt!\NHe's probably as bad as Honza. Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.85,0:07:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the leader at that orphanage,\Nweren't you, Antonio?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.26,0:07:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not really the leader.\NI'm just a little older than everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.60,0:07:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now about that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.84,0:07:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it about Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.37,0:07:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.87,0:07:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that Honza and Izzy\Nwere asked about Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.71,0:07:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah. And?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.81,0:07:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a nice person.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.22,0:07:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Mr. Grimmer a suspect?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.52,0:07:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No...I'm not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer isn't the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.69,0:07:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pedrov and Mrs. Anna were killed\Nwhen we got back from playing soccer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.30,0:08:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I told this to\Nthe police already, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.40,0:08:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw a beautiful blonde woman\Ncome out of our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.78,0:08:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to arrest him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.41,0:08:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.58,0:08:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.11,0:08:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No. That hasn't\Nbeen decided yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.66,0:08:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I promised him! We've decided\Nwhere we're going to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.53,0:08:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell me where that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.44,0:08:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.84,0:08:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it all right?\NI might arrest him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.54,0:08:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's no way\Nthat he'd murder anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.82,0:09:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.63,0:09:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!\N– Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.86,0:09:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while.\NHow've you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.20,0:09:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.30,0:09:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't been crying,\Nhave you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.60,0:09:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He's wet his bed twice!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.47,0:09:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I wet my bed until I was\Nmuch older than you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.51,0:09:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\N– What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.38,0:09:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Antonio, do you have\Nthe thing I gave you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.32,0:09:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI'm glad you held on to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.70,0:09:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something important that\Nyour grandfather left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.57,0:09:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.37,0:09:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have much time.\NEveryone, take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.01,0:09:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's play soccer,\NMr. Grimmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.71,0:09:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Sorry.\NI really don't have the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.18,0:09:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me introduce you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.88,0:09:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,These are our new friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.32,0:10:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! I'll play just a little!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.22,0:10:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!\N– All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.10,0:10:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Go! There's a chance.\NPass it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.17,0:10:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They took it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.61,0:10:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That dribbling isn't\Ngood enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.01,0:10:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Try harder as a defender!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.09,0:10:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You got me there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.79,0:10:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I go.\NThere!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.31,0:10:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Mr. Grimmer,\Naren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.41,0:11:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you come to arrest me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.41,0:11:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in front of children.\NDon't wave around a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.72,0:11:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Toss me your gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.39,0:11:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.96,0:11:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you throw it away?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.29,0:11:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never walked\Naround with a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.40,0:11:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you kill Inspector Zeman?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.40,0:11:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.51,0:11:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I was half-dead\Nfrom being tortured.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Your nails...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.28,0:11:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't shoot the gun.\NI might have killed the other two.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.79,0:11:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.56,0:11:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.36,0:11:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you resting?! We don't have\Nenough members on our team!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.37,0:12:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break!\NI'm worn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.91,0:12:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked the children to\Ninvite you to play soccer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.01,0:12:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been watching you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.71,0:12:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you think?\NAm I the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.92,0:12:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.69,0:12:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people betrayed me\Nthese past few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.92,0:12:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to\Nbelieve in anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.69,0:12:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only\Nbelieve in yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.83,0:12:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, you're all\Nthat you can believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.67,0:12:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to arrest me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.01,0:12:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you promise me\Nthat you won't run away?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.68,0:12:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you staying right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.02,0:12:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Pavla Hotel, room 302...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.29,0:12:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Come by when you're sure\NI'm the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.76,0:13:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll let you hold on to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.93,0:13:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's the cause of\Nall these incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.37,0:13:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the key to a safe deposit box.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.81,0:13:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This sign? It's pretty old.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.28,0:13:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the sign for\Na pub 200 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.09,0:13:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been up even though\Nthe pub is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.26,0:13:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's completely faded,\Nbut it's a landmark even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.33,0:13:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There have been wars and disasters.\NIt's amazing it survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.54,0:13:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There was even a fire\Nabout a decade ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.34,0:13:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.54,0:13:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. A woman with a child moved\Ninto the second floor here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.31,0:13:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She was a beautiful woman,\Nbut she was kind of somber.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.38,0:13:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She hardly ever went out.\NIt seems she was using an alias.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.06,0:14:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, a black car\Ntook her and her kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.36,0:14:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman was rumored
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.00,0:14:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to have participated in\Nanti-government activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.20,0:14:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That sort of thing happened\Noften in those days.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.97,0:14:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a government of terror during\Nthe final stages of communism.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.34,0:14:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a terrible time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.48,0:14:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't unusual for\Nsomeone to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.78,0:14:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Did that woman have\Ntwins with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No. She only had one child.\NA real pretty one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.16,0:14:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a boy or a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.13,0:14:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Come to think of it,\Nwhich was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.03,0:14:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you can't tell\Nthe difference when they're little.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.74,0:14:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.44,0:14:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was saying that taking\Naway the mother is one thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.44,0:14:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but taking away an innocent child\Nis too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.88,0:14:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when the fire started.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.58,0:15:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think that anyone\Nwas in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.18,0:15:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But when the fire started coming out\Nfrom there, I found the child inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.66,0:15:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The child was probably released,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.13,0:15:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,got hungry and started the fire\Nto cook something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.33,0:15:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is the child?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.47,0:15:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where it went afterwards.\NI wonder what happened to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.71,0:15:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What if that child\Nwas one of the twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.54,0:15:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.88,0:15:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What if one child was taken and\Nthe other was left in that room?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.21,0:15:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. That's another\Nway to think of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.59,0:15:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But why do you care\Nso much if they're twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.70,0:15:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That tall guy, Grimmer, that\Nyou said I should check out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.54,0:15:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think he's the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.74,0:15:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.68,0:16:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for saying something\Nso groundless, Mr. Suk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.25,0:16:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.38,0:16:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned a lot of things\Nfrom following him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.69,0:16:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, I thought this was a battle\Nto avenge Inspector Zeman.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.52,0:16:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I was frantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.36,0:16:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But as I learned more,\NI discovered that Inspector Zeman,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.33,0:16:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the detective I looked up to,\Nwas corrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.97,0:16:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, my head chief and two\Nof my superiors were poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.91,0:16:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I was shocked when I\Nreceived word of the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.98,0:16:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, "How far has darkness\Nspread throughout this world?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.69,0:16:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.99,0:16:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Czechoslovakian secret police\Nare behind these incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They were an organization that was\Nunder the direct supervision of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.86,0:16:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the Internal Affairs Ministry\Nduring the former government.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.09,0:16:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They were tools of\Nthe Soviet Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.40,0:16:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But they were disbanded\Nnearly ten years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.80,0:16:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,during the democratic revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.90,0:17:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Their leaders were put on trial,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.04,0:17:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but several of them\Nescaped underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.27,0:17:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, they're planning to\Ntake back their former power.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,At least I know that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.55,0:17:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But why must they claim\Nso many victims?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.12,0:17:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Was this incident really\Nonly their doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.75,0:17:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows how closely
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.16,0:17:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the darkness has encroached\Nupon the world we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.19,0:17:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe in anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.70,0:17:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But Mr. Grimmer told me that\NI can only believe in myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.27,0:17:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that when he entrusted me\Nwith a certain something. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.64,0:17:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep talking about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.41,0:17:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.31,0:17:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don't know your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.52,0:17:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... It's all right!\NYou don't have to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.12,0:17:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that people\Ngained trust in each other
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.46,0:18:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when they learn each other's\Nnames and pasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.33,0:18:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But...I can talk so much\Nabout anything to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.48,0:18:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents are both teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.11,0:18:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But my father participated\Nin democratic activities,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.02,0:18:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so the authorities had\Ntheir eyes on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.02,0:18:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother broke up with\Nmy father to protect me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.39,0:18:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother was fiercely opposed to\Nthe idea of me becoming a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.96,0:18:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you want to\Nbecome a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.70,0:18:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,My friends said why\Nat that bar, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.43,0:18:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that you really did\Nwatch too many detective dramas?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.14,0:18:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my childhood dream.\NI always played detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.84,0:18:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.22,0:18:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't laugh so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.98,0:18:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.40,0:19:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So what were you\Nentrusted with?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.87,0:19:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.14,0:19:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, you said that Grimmer\Nentrusted you with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.91,0:19:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... It's a key to\Na safe deposit box.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.45,0:19:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A safe deposit box?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.11,0:19:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that something\Nreally important is in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.39,0:19:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Pedrov, a German man who was\Nrunning an illegal orphanage,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,was killed recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.86,0:19:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.09,0:19:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside the safe deposit box
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.59,0:19:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is the data from Pedrov's\Nhuman experiments or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.80,0:19:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that that's the cause\Nof all these events.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.44,0:19:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.71,0:19:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell anyone, even the police,\Nanything about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.74,0:19:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But this isn't something\NI can handle by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.45,0:19:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.71,0:19:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.98,0:20:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why your mother didn't\Nwant you to become a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.12,0:20:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She was worried that\Nsomething might happen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.29,0:20:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a very bad feeling!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.46,0:20:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't tell anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.26,0:20:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel the same way\Nabout you as your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.01,0:20:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.02,0:20:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,My name...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.62,0:20:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.02,0:20:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.76,0:20:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.39,0:20:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna... That's a nice name.\NSo you are German.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.93,0:20:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.74,0:20:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.47,0:21:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, Mr. Tulunka
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.97,0:21:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... It's a nice night,\Nisn't it, Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.48,0:21:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good evening, Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.58,0:21:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, Mrs. Jalka.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.57,0:22:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A safe deposit box key...
